# x86_64 Darwin hex0 seed.
#
# This file is the trusted seed, in the same spirit as oriansj/stage0:
# every emitted byte is visible, and each line explains the corresponding
# Mach-O field or machine instruction.  The build first materializes this
# file with the small C hex0 materializer, then proves the materialized
# program is self-hosting by assembling this file again byte-for-byte.
#
# Interface: hex0 INPUT OUTPUT
# Syntax: pairs of hexadecimal nybbles; whitespace is ignored; # and ; start
# comments.  The output file is created with mode 0700.

